bug.short_desc: SelectBox doesn't close or move the opened list.

long_desc.thetext: There is no simple solution for this problem. Maybe it is possible to keep track of position changes if we add another bubbling event for the mouse wheel and add listener for all related widgets (popups, tooltips etc.).

The fix has the problem that the pop-up is shown all the time, even though the SelectBox isn't visible in the view port.
See next screenshot.

Created attachment 426 screenshot
Shows that the SelectBox isn't visible, because the view port has moved, but the pop-up is shown.
The best way is to close the pop-up if the user do a scroll action with the view.
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
